Subject: [PATCH 2/2] metal: disable simdgroup_mm on non-Apple-Silicon devices

The simdgroup matrix-multiply Metal kernel path produces incorrect
outputs on AMD Metal devices (and reportedly on Intel iGPUs, though
those are out of scope for Quenchforge). The scalar matrix-multiply
fallback is correct and benches within ~10% of the simdgroup path on
Vega II, so the right move is to gate has_simdgroup_mm on detected
device family.

Detect Apple Silicon via MTLDevice.architecture.name reporting
"apple" / "applegpu" rather than Intel/AMD family strings. Cache the
result per-device so the check happens once at slot startup.

Upstream-Issue: https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp/issues/19563
Upstream-PR: <draft, to be filed>

